                        <msContents>
                            <summary>
                                <p>The manuscript is missing up to 70 leaves. 23 leaves are today found in the manuscript, <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100039">Kassel</placeName>, Universitätsbibliothek Kassel, <ref target="https://orka.bibliothek.uni-kassel.de/viewer/image/1399889576500/1/LOG_0000/">Ms. math. 50</ref>. One leaf is found in <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100078">Stockholm</placeName>, Nationalmuseum, NBM 2409. One more leaf was sold by <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100190">Dr. Jörn Günther Rare Books</orgName> to a private collector in <date when="1995"/>. The content of the manuscript has been placed in the wrong order (most likely when the manuscript was rebound in the 18th or 19th century). The table of content at the end (<locus from="164r" to="165r" scheme="folios"/>) may indicate the origianal order of the texts. It is primarily the texts found on <locus from="26r" to="49v" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="55r" to="58v" scheme="folios"/> that have been placed in the wrong place in the manuscript.</p>
                            </summary>
                            <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="2r" to="2v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Prayer</title>
                                <rubric>Oratio ad faciem redemptoris nostri </rubric>
                                <incipit>SAlue sancta facies</incipit>
                                <explicit>securi uideamus te christum dominum nostrum Amen</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="3r" to="54v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Hours for the week</title>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="3r" to="6v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Hours of the Trinity (Sundays)</title>
                                    <rubric>Incipiunt hore de sancta trinitate pro diebus dominicis</rubric>
                                    <incipit>Domine labia mea aperies [...] QUicumque vult animam suam</incipit>
                                    <explicit>Faciat me credere hoc cum firmitate Amen Benedicamus domino Deo gratias</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="7r" to="10v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="uniform">Hours for the dead (Mondays)</title>
                                    <rubric>Incipiunt hore defuncotrum pro die lune </rubric>
                                    <incipit>CIrcumdederunt me gemitus mortis</incipit>
                                    <explicit>Effici glorificas tua satias uisione Requiescant in pace Amen </explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="11r" to="14v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Hours of the Holy Spirit (Tuesdays)</title>
                                    <rubric>Incipiunt hore de sancto spiritu pro die martis</rubric>
                                    <incipit>DOmine labia mea aperies <gap reason="editorial"/> NObis sancti spiritus gracia sit data</incipit>
                                    <explicit>Ut vivamus iugiter in celi regione Benedicamus domino Deo gratias</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="15r" to="17v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Hours for all saints (Wednesdays)</title>
                                    <rubric>Incipiunt hore de omnibus sanctis pro die mercurii</rubric>
                                    <incipit>DOmine labia mea aperies <gap reason="editorial"/> SAncta dei genitrix</incipit>
                                    <explicit>Rogetis absque aliqua intermissione Amen Benedicamus domino Deo gratias</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="18r" to="21v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Hours of the Eucharist (Thursdays)</title>
                                    <rubric>Incipiunt hore de sanctissmo sacramento altaris pro die iouis </rubric>
                                    <incipit>DOmine laba mea aperies <gap reason="editorial"/> COrporis misterium pange gloriosi</incipit>
                                    <explicit>Ualeam te sumere cum deuotione Amen Benedicamus domino Deo gratias</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="22r" to="25r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Hours of the Holy Cross (Fridays)</title>
                                    <rubric>Incipiunt hore sancte crucis pro die veneris </rubric>
                                    <incipit>DOmine labia mea aperies <gap reason="editorial"/> PAtris sapientia ueritas diuina</incipit>
                                    <explicit>sic labori consonans consors sim corone Amen Benedicamus domino Deo gratias</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="26r" to="48v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Instructions for mass and various masses</title>
                                    <rubric>Quando sacerdos offert hostiam super altare dicit hanc orationem</rubric>
                                    <msItem>
                                        <locus from="26r" to="34v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <title type="desc">Instructions for mass</title>
                                    </msItem>
                                    <msItem>
                                        <locus from="35r" to="38v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <title type="desc">Mass for the Virgin Mary for the entire year</title>
                                    </msItem>
                                    <msItem>
                                        <locus from="39r" to="40v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <title type="desc">Mass for the Trinity</title>
                                    </msItem>
                                    <msItem>
                                        <locus from="41r" to="42v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <title type="desc">Mass for all saints</title>
                                    </msItem>
                                    <msItem>
                                        <locus from="43r" to="44v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <title type="uniform">Mass for Corpus Christi</title>
                                    </msItem>
                                    <msItem>
                                        <locus from="45r" to="46r" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <title type="desc">Mass for the Holy Cross</title>
                                    </msItem>
                                    <msItem>
                                        <locus from="46v" to="47v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <title type="desc">Mass for the dead</title>
                                        <note>
                                            <p>After <locus from="47" to="47" scheme="folios"/> a leaf is missing with resulting loss of text.</p>
                                            <p/>
                                        </note>
                                    </msItem>
                                    <msItem>
                                        <locus from="48r" to="48v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <title type="desc">Office to the Virgin Mary</title>
                                        <incipit>O Beatissima virgo maria ego misserimus peccator</incipit>
                                        <explicit>ac honor noster defendatur ad salutem corporis et anime Per christum dominum nostrum Amen</explicit>
                                    </msItem>
                                    <msItem>
                                        <locus from="49r" to="49v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <title type="desc">Suffrage to St Sebald</title>
                                        <rubric>De sancto Sebaldo confessore</rubric>
                                        <incipit>SSAncte sebalde qui ex regali stripe originem ducens</incipit>
                                        <explicit>ac defensionem ad salutem corporis et anime consequamur Per dominum noster ihesum christum et cetera</explicit>
                                        <note>
                                            <locus from="50" to="50" scheme="folios"/>: ruled, but no text.</note>
                                    </msItem>
                                    <incipit>SUscipe sancte pater omnipotens </incipit>
                                    <explicit>sit te miserante propitiabile Per christum dominum nostrum Amen</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="51r" to="54v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Hours of the Virgin (Saturdays)</title>
                                    <rubric>Incipiunt hore beatissime uirginis Marie pro diebus sabbatis</rubric>
                                    <incipit>DOmine laba mea aperies <gap reason="editorial"/> DEus qui cunctum hominem de limo terr creauit</incipit>
                                    <explicit>Precum suarum feruore ut in celum tecum simus Amen Bendicamus domino Deo gratias</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="55r" to="58v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Mass for the Virgin Mary</title>
                                <rubric>Incipiunt missa beate marie uirginis</rubric>
                                <incipit>INtroibo ad altare dei</incipit>
                                <explicit>qui tecum uiuit et regnat in vnitate spiritus sancti deus Per omnia secula seculorum Amen</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="59r" to="64r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Readings from the Gospels</title>
                                <rubric>Inicium sancti euangeli secundum iohannem</rubric>
                                <incipit>In principio erat uerbum </incipit>
                                <explicit>et sermonem confirmante sequentibus signis Deo gratias</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="59r" to="59r" scheme="folios"/>: John;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="60v" to="60v" scheme="folios"/>: Luke;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="62r" to="62r" scheme="folios"/>: Matthew;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="63v" to="63v" scheme="folios"/>: Mark;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="64v" to="64v" scheme="folios"/> ruled, but no text.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="65r" to="76v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Mass for holy days</title>
                                <rubric>In die sancto pasche ad missam introitus</rubric>
                                <incipit>REsurrexi et adhuc tecum sum alleluya</incipit>
                                <explicit>Qui tecum viuit et regnat in vnitate spiritus sancti deus per omnia secula seculorum Amen</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="65r" to="65r" scheme="folios"/>: Easter;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="69r" to="69r" scheme="folios"/>: Pentecost;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="73r" to="73r" scheme="folios"/>: Christmas;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="77" to="78" scheme="folios"/>: ruled, but no text.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="79r" to="115v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Hours of the Virgin Mary, Use of Rome</title>
                                <rubric>Incipiunt hore beate marie uirginis secundum cursum ecclesie romane </rubric>
                                <incipit>DOmine laba mea aperies <gap reason="editorial"/> Inuitatorium Aue maria gratia plena</incipit>
                                <explicit>Domine exaudi oratione meam Et clamor meus ad te ueniat Benedicamus domino deo gratias Fidelium anime per misericordiam dei requiescant in pace Amen</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locusGrp>
                                            <locus from="88v" to="88v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="95v" to="95v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="104v" to="104v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="107v" to="107v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="112v" to="112v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="116" to="116" scheme="folios"/>
                                        </locusGrp>: ruled, but no text.</p>
                                    <p> After <locus from="116" to="116" scheme="folios"/> two leaves are missing. The preceeding text is complete and text on <locus from="117r" to="117r" scheme="folios"/> is the start of The Seven Penitential psalms.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="117r" to="123r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Seven penitential psalms</title>
                                <rubric>Incipiunt septem psalmi pentenciales</rubric>
                                <incipit>DOmine ne in furore tuo arguas</incipit>
                                <explicit>neque vindictam sumas de peccatis nostris</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="123r" to="127v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Litany</title>
                                <rubric>Letania</rubric>
                                <incipit>KYrielesion Christeleison</incipit>
                                <explicit>Qui viuis et regnas deus Per omnia secula seculorum Amen </explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <locus from="128" to="128" scheme="folios"/>: ruled, but no text.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="129r" to="138v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Prayers, sequences, and hymns</title>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="129r" to="130r" scheme="folios"/>
